---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
---

<Layout title="Characters">
    <style>
        /* First, you define the shape of the elements. In this case, we're using circles and rectangles */
        .blurry-circle, .blurry-rectangle {
            position: absolute;
            background: violet;
            border-radius: 50%; /* This makes the shape a circle */
            opacity: 0.4;

            z-index: -1;
        }

        .blurry-rectangle {
            border-radius: 0%; /* Reset the border-radius to make the shape a rectangle */
        }

        /* Then, you can specify the size and position of each shape individually */
        .blurry-circle {
            top: 75%;
            left: 20%;
            width: 300px;
            height: 300px;
        }

        .blurry-rectangle {
            bottom: 40%;
            right: 15%;
            width: 200px;
            height: 200px;
        }

        .main_background {
            position: relative;
        }
    </style>
    <div class="blurry-circle top-[50%] left-[55%]"></div>
    <div class="blurry-rectangle top-[75%] left-[0%] w-[125px]"></div>
    <div id="main_background" class="main_background backdrop-blur-3xl">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 ">
            <section class="py-8 px-4 text-center">
                <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-gray-900">Characters</h2>
                <p class="py-16 mt-2 text-lg text-gray-600">The characters found within the Great Gastby are complex figures who's motivations and actions reflect the centeral theme of the corruption of the American Dream. Each embody different aspects of the American Dream and it's corruption and decay in the Roaring Twenties.</p>
            </section>
            <section class="py-4 flex">
                <div class="shadow-xl p-4 rounded-xl bg-gray-50 border-2 border-slate-200 w-2/3">
                    <h1 class="font-bold text-4xl ">Jay Gatsby</h1>
                    <img class="transition ease-in-out  rounded-xl my-5 hover:scale-105" src="https://pyxis.nymag.com/v1/imgs/569/1ea/c83e965e2cb689eb97b6e688bb619c5c7a-12-gatsbyintro.2x.rhorizontal.w700.jpg"/>
                    <p class="text-lg">A self made man who ammasses a large fortune. He personifies the most ambitious form of the American Dream, and the desire for great wealth. Dispite his wealth, Gatsby remains an outsider to the upper class, and his dreams with Daisy remain unfulfilled. That reflects the unattainable nature of the American Dream.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="py-4 flex">
                <div class="w-1/2"></div>
                <div class="shadow-xl p-4 rounded-xl bg-gray-50 border-2 border-slate-200 w-2/3">
                    <h1 class="font-bold text-4xl ">Daisy Buchanan</h1>
                    <img class="transition ease-in-out  rounded-xl my-5 hover:scale-105 w-full" src="https://rebeccaelizabethp.files.wordpress.com/2013/05/thegreatgatsbydaisy.jpg"/>
                    <p class="text-lg">Daisy is the embodyment of aristocracy and the object of Gatsby's desire. She is shallow, careless, and ultimately unfulfilled. Daisy represents the hollowness at the heart of the American Dream.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="py-4 flex">
                <div class="shadow-xl p-4 rounded-xl bg-gray-50 border-2 border-slate-200 w-2/3">
                    <h1 class="font-bold text-4xl ">Nick Carraway</h1>
                    <img class="transition ease-in-out  rounded-xl my-5 hover:scale-105 w-full" src="https://weharttwilight.weebly.com/uploads/2/8/1/0/28104033/121331931.jpg"/>
                    <p class="text-lg">Nick represents the disillusionment with the American Dream. Despite being part of the social circle, Nick maintains a certain detachment and moral judgment. His disillusionment reflects the overall disenchantment with the American Dream.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="w-1/2"></div>
            </section>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>